<subSubSection id="09AB84DA4214894CFF7559E3FB95C3FB" pageId="19" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="410ED7514214894CFF7559E3FE91C28A" blockId="19.[227,341,684,710]" box="[227,341,684,710]" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">
<heading id="1A46603D4214894CFF7559E3FE91C28A" bold="true" box="[227,341,684,710]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="29" reason="3">
<emphasis id="73C50B434214894CFF7559E3FE91C28A" bold="true" box="[227,341,684,710]" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="410ED7514214894CFF755992FB95C3FB" blockId="19.[227,1438,733,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">
The lineage of the family 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD24214894CFDB75992FD6DC2BB" authorityName="Korn" authorityYear="2001" box="[545,681,733,759]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Taouzitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="19" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Taouzitidae</taxonomicName>
partly resembles the morphological evolution of two Frasnian lineages of gephuroceratids, the koenenitids and the beloceratoids (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="2520AAA04214894CFBCD584BFB26C351" author="Korn D." box="[1115,1250,771,798]" pageId="19" pageNumber="29" pagination="193 - 215" refId="ref18127" refString="Korn D. 2001. Morphometric evolution and phylogeny of Palaeozoic ammonoids. Early and Middle Devonian. Acta Geologica Polonica 51: 193 - 215." type="journal article" year="2001">Korn 2001</bibRefCitation>
). However, the major difference between the taouzitids and the beloceratids is that in the taouzitids the external lobe retained its original shape, whereas in the beloceratids there was a proliferation of both the umbilical lobes and the external lobes. In the koenenitids, the external lobe remained tripartite and there was the development of only three umbilical lobes in the terminal genus 
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD24214894CFC4E58D2FB8EC3FA" authorityName="Mojsisovics" authorityYear="1882" box="[984,1098,925,950]" class="Fusulinata" family="Schwagerinidae" genus="Timanites" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fusulinida" pageId="19" pageNumber="29" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B434214894CFC4E58D2FB8EC3FA" box="[984,1098,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">Timanites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
